article.headline: North Florida 70, Palm Beach Atlantic 62
article.story: JACKSONVILLE, Fla. -- Eni Cuka scored 18 points on 7-of-11 shooting and North Florida beat Palm Beach Atlantic 70-62 on Saturday. The Ospreys (2-8) hit 13 of 17 free throws in the second half and turned the ball over three times, compared to 10 in the first half, to overcome a 34-28 halftime deficit. In the first half, Palm Beach Atlantic was 5-for-11 from 3-point range and David Powell scored 11 of his 16 points. Stan Januska scored 15 of his 17 points in the second half as North Florida outscored the Sailfish 42-28 in the frame. Palm Beach Atlantic led 42-36 with 11:42 left to play, but the Osprey went on a 14-3 run, highlighted by six points from Januska to take a 50-46 lead with 7:25 remaining in the game. Chris Joseph added 12 points for the Sailfish.
